@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home Page";
}

<div class="text-center">
    <h1 class="display-4 ">Welcome to WebSchool</h1>

    <div class="row mt-5">
        <p class="col-md-8 offset-2 text-justify">WebSchool is trying to make the e-learning and e-teaching experience more pleasent and easy for everyone. There is an easy way of making, editing and giving assignments for the teachers. They also have a choice... They can let the system automatically check every assignment and calcuate the student grade or they can do it manually. As for the students, there is a simple way to solve assignments. Just few clicks. There is also a social side of the system. Every school has it's own forum. There you can find help by creating new post, give help by commenting under a post or just notify everybody of something that you thing is remarkable :). Go, leave mark behing you !</p>
    </div>

    <div class="row mt-5">
        <div class="card col-md-4 offset-4">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title text-justify">Create new School System</h5>
                <p class="card-text text-justify">With few clicks you can create your own School System with full support of post and comments. Classes, subjects, assignemnts and many more :) Come on, Join us!</p>
                <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="CreateUser" class="btn btn-primary w-100">Let's Go</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
